        the following manner: <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">two</NUMEX> replicates of approximately <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">60</NUMEX>
        <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">plants</ENAMEX> each for the following entries <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">N2</TIMEX>, 
        bmr2, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">N3</TIMEX>, 
        bmr3, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">N4</TIMEX>, 
        bmr4, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">N6</TIMEX>, 
        bmr6, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">N7</TIMEX>, 
        bmr7, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">N12</TIMEX>, 
        bmr12, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">N18</TIMEX>, 
        bmr18, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">N19</TIMEX>, and 
        bmr19. The 
        bmr mutations were introduced via
        <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">chemical</ENAMEX> mutagenesis with diethyl sulfate-ethylsulfonate
